SpNote.note:
In the thermal its necessary for the standards to have the same exposure as the target, so that non-linearity is not an issue. For this reason the standards here are set to use the largest field field possible on the assumption that the target is being observed in this way. The largest field is the full array for L' and the 512x512 subarray at M'. Adjust the configuration to match your target but be careful to use appropriate exposures - see the web pages.
Efficiency is very low in large field mode; for maximum efficiency the 0.06"/pixel camera should be used with the 512x512 subarray.
SpNote.title: Field size and efficiency

SpNote.note:
In the thermal its necessary for the standards to have the same exposure as the target, so that non-linearity is not an issue. The standards here are setup for peak efficiency, using the 0.06"/pixel camera and the 512x512 subarray. Adjust the configuration to match your target but be careful to use appropriate exposures - see the web pages.
The largest field available is with the 0.12"/pixel camera and full array at L', 512x512 at M'. Observations are then very inefficient.
